The paper focuses on improving the visual aspect of visual relationship detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and preprocessing methods also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation metrics used, such as Recall@1 and error analysis, are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
